[ProMED-mail thanks Sonny Inbaraj Krishnan for forwarding this information to us. Descriptions of the 1st 3 cases in Cambodia in the current year (2013) are available in the preceding ProMED-mail posing Avian influenza, human (01): Cambodia, fatalities 20130125.1514597. Perhaps the most significant feature of these recent cases in Cambodia is the high proportion of fatalities and that children have been the most vulnerable. Parents and guardians are urged to keep children away from sick or dead poultry, discourage them from playing in areas where there are poultry.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Cambodia can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1iGB. - Mod.CP]
